Tata Power Aims for 300 Megawatt Solar Capacity in 4 to 5 Years

-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 
2011-04-27T07:44:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/tata-power-aims-for-300-megawatt-solar-capacity-in-4-to-5-years.html
Tata Power Co. plans to have a
capacity to generate 300 megawatts of solar power in four to
five years, S. Ramakrishnan, executive director of finance, said
in Mumbai today. It costs as much as 170 million rupees to
generate one megawatt of solar power, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pratish Narayanan in Mumbai at 
 pnarayanan9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
